29:58.100 --> 29:59.449
- Alex, Kevin, congratulations.

29:59.580 --> 30:00.842
You guys are in the third

30:00.973 --> 30:02.713
and final round
of this competition,

30:02.844 --> 30:04.977
which means that you're both
one step closer to the title

30:05.107 --> 30:07.457
of "Forged in Fire" champion
and a check for $10,000.

30:07.588 --> 30:09.982
All you need to do now
is go home and re-create

30:10.112 --> 30:12.593
this iconic weapon
from history.

30:15.683 --> 30:17.250
The spatha.

30:19.905 --> 30:21.471
The spatha
was a vicious sword

30:21.602 --> 30:23.822
given to infantry during
the Roman Empire.

30:23.952 --> 30:25.693
The double-edged weapon
was used to inflict

30:25.824 --> 30:27.738
deep slashes and deadly cuts
on their enemies

30:27.869 --> 30:29.653
while the tapered tip
was effective for thrusting.

30:29.784 --> 30:31.307
In the third
and fourth centuries,

30:31.438 --> 30:32.874
some of these
Roman soldiers turned sides

30:33.005 --> 30:34.397
and became Barbarians.

30:34.528 --> 30:35.746
They then used the spatha

30:35.877 --> 30:37.444
in wars against
the Roman Empire,

30:37.574 --> 30:39.141
and eventually led
to its demise.

30:39.272 --> 30:41.187
Ancient Rome continues
to be the backdrop

30:41.317 --> 30:43.319
for blockbuster films
like "Gladiator,"

30:43.450 --> 30:47.367
in which the spatha
can be seen wielded in battle.

30:47.497 --> 30:50.370
Gentlemen, your final challenge
is to forge a spatha.

30:50.500 --> 30:53.852
Your blades must be between
27 and 29 inches in length.

30:53.982 --> 30:56.419
They must have a medial ridge
on both sides of the blade,

30:56.550 --> 30:58.204
and it must be double edged.

30:58.334 --> 31:00.641
It must have a wooden guard,
and a disk pommel.

31:00.771 --> 31:02.773
You'll have just four days
at your home forges

31:02.904 --> 31:04.514
