40:20.548 --> 40:23.377
Kevin, your blade must
fall within our parameters

40:23.508 --> 40:25.945
in order to be tested
evenly and fairly

40:26.075 --> 40:27.512
with your competitors.

40:27.642 --> 40:30.166
Your blade does not have
a central ridge.

40:30.297 --> 40:31.994
That was a parameter
that was outlined

40:32.125 --> 40:33.387
before we ever
sent you home.

40:33.518 --> 40:34.867
And for that reason,

40:34.997 --> 40:37.043
you cannot be
the "Forged in Fire" champion.

40:37.173 --> 40:38.827
Come on, my friend.

40:38.958 --> 40:41.482
- You know, it's just a bummer
I can't see it tested.

40:41.613 --> 40:44.354
That's what I really wanted.
I want to see how it holds up.

40:44.485 --> 40:45.617
- Nice work on that handle,
though.

40:45.747 --> 40:47.270
- Thank you,
I appreciate it.

40:47.401 --> 40:50.752
When I was making it,
it had the defined ridge in it.

40:50.883 --> 40:52.798
Just with the sanding
and grinding,

40:52.928 --> 40:54.408
it just took more of it off.

40:54.539 --> 40:56.366
But this whole experience
has been a blast.

40:56.497 --> 40:57.933
Congratulations.

40:58.064 --> 40:59.457
This isn't a loss.

40:59.587 --> 41:02.024
I'm coming home with
a $10,000 experience.

41:04.070 --> 41:07.508
- Alex, you made a sharp
and deadly spatha.

41:07.639 --> 41:09.205
But not only that,
you made something

41:09.336 --> 41:11.860
that is detailed and beautiful.

41:11.991 --> 41:14.994
Your attention to detail
has elevated you

41:15.124 --> 41:17.257
to the title of
"Forged in Fire" champion.

41:17.387 --> 41:18.737
Congratulations.

41:18.867 --> 41:21.783
Your title comes with
a check for $10,000.

41:21.914 --> 41:23.176
Good job, brother.

41:23.306 --> 41:24.569
- This is pretty wild.

41:24.699 --> 41:26.484
I came here
to challenge myself

41:26.614 --> 41:28.747
and put myself through
a super rigorous test

41:28.877 --> 41:30.618
and I came out on top,
and it feels great.

41:30.749 --> 41:32.707
This $10,000,

41:32.838 --> 41:35.405
I'm actually gonna give it
all straight to my parents.

41:35.536 --> 41:37.407
They supported me
through college

41:37.538 --> 41:38.887
as I was learning
bladesmithing

41:39.018 --> 41:40.498
and they're both
getting ready to retire.

41:40.628 --> 41:42.804
So it's all going to them.
